ld V.|author2=Butt, John|access-date=6 April 2018|url=https://doi.org/10.1093/gmo/9781561592630.article.50932}}\n*{{citation|title=Hans Holbein and Miles Coverdale: A New Woodcut|first1=David|last1= Paisey|first2= Giulia|last2= Bartrum|\njournal=Print Quarterly|volume=26|issue=3|year=2009|pages=227\u2013253|jstor=43826083}}\n*{{citation|first=J.A.|last=Reincken|authorlink=Johann Adam Reincken|title=Complete Organ Works|isbn=978-3795797737|editor-last=Dirksen|editor-first=Pieter|publisher=[[Breitkopf & H\u00e4rtel]]|chapter=Preface|year=2005|pages=7\u201310, 83}}\n*{{citation|first=J.A.|last=Reincken|authorlink=Johann Adam Reincken|title=Complete Organ Works|edition=2nd|ismn=9790001137416|editor-last=Beckmann|editor-first=Klaus|publisher=[[Schott Music]]|chapter=Preface, Critical commentary, Facsimiles|year=2008|pages=9\u201312, 58\u201361, 61\u201364}}\n*{{GroveOnline|title=Sch\u00fctz, Heinrich||author= Rifkin, Joshua|author2=Linfield, Eva|author3=McCulloch, Derek|author4=Baron, Stephen|access-date=12 March 2018|url=https://doi.org/10.1093/gmo/9781561592630.article.45997}}\n*{{citation|title=The Routledge Research Companion to Johann Sebastian Bach|editor-first=Robin A. |editor-last=Leaver|publisher=Taylor & Francis| year=2017|isbn=9781409417903|chapter=The Alt-Bachisches Archiv|first=Steven|last=Rose|page=213\u2013236}}\n*{{citation|first=Arnold|last= Schering|title=Johann Philipp Kirnberger als Herausgeber Bachscher Chor\u00e4le|journal= Bach-Jahrbuch|volume=15|year=1918|pages=141\u2013149}}\n*{{citation|title=J.S. Bach|series=Oxford composer companions|editor=Malcolm Boyd|editor2=John Butt|publisher=[[Oxford University Press]]|year=2003|edition=2nd|isbn=0198606206|chapter=Stylus Phantasticus|last=Schulenberg|first=David|page=[https://archive.org/details/jsbach0000unse/page/471 471]|chapter-url=https://archive.org/details/jsbach0000unse/page/471}}\n*{{citation|last=Schulenberg|first= David|title=The keyboard music of J.S. Bach|edition=2nd|year=2006|publisher=[[Routledge]]|isbn=0415974003}}\n*{{citation|first=Hans-Joachim|last=Schulze|journal=Bach-Jahrbuch|volume=69|year=1983|pages=81\u2013100|language=de|title=150 St\u00fcck von den Bachischen Erben}}\n*{{citation|title=J.S. Bach, the Breitkopfs, and Eighteenth-century Music Trade|series=Bach Perspectives|volume=2|editor=George B. Stauffer|publisher=[[University of Nebraska Press]]|year= 1996|isbn=0803210442|first=Hans-Joachim|last=Schulze|chapter=J.S. Bach's Vocal Works in the Breitkopf Nonthematic Catalogs of 1761 to 1836|pages=35\u201352}}\n*{{citation |last1=Sch\u00fctz |first1=Heinrich |author-link1=Heinrich Sch\u00fctz |date=1628 |chapter=Der CXXXVII. Psalm |chapter-url=http://daten.digitale-sammlungen.de/bsb00094385/image_572 |title=Psalmen Davids: Hiebevorn in Teutzsche Reimen gebracht durch D. Cornelium Beckern |language=de |location=Freiberg |publisher=Georg Hoffman |pages=560\u2013564 |postscript=. {{RISM|00000990058712}} |title-link=Psalmen Davids: Hiebevorn in Teutzsche Reimen gebracht durch D. Cornelium Beckern }}\n*{{citation|last1=Sch\u00fctz |first1=Heinrich |author-link1=Heinrich Sch\u00fctz |translator-last=Johnston |translator-first=Gregory S. |date=2013 |title=A Heinrich Sch\u00fctz Reader: Letters and Documents in Translation |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=F3VTON3VMDoC |location=United States |publisher= [[Oxford University Press]] |page=[https://books.google.com/books?id=F3VTON3VMDoC&pg=PA62 62] |isbn=978-0199812202}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Shannon |first1=John R. |date=2012 |title=The Evolution of Organ Music in the 17th Century: A Study of European Styles |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GB64QIHirTEC |publisher=McFarland |isbn=9780786488667 |ref=harv}}\n*{{GroveOnline|title=Schein, Johann Hermann||author= Snyder, Kerala Y.|author2=Johnson, Gregory S.|access-date=12 March 2018|url=https://doi.org/10.1093/gmo/9781561592630.article.24787}}\n*{{citation|last=Spagnoli|first=Gina|title=The Early Baroque Era: From the late 16th century to the 1660s|chapter=Dresden at the Time of Heinrich Sch\u00fctz|editor-last=Price|editor-first=Curtis|publisher=[[Macmillan Publishers|Macmillan]]|year=1993|pages=164\u2013184}}\n*{{citation|url=https://archive.org/details/bachorgelbuchlei0000stin/page/2|title=Bach: The Orgelb\u00fcchlein|year=1999|first=Russell|last=Stinson|publisher=[[Oxford University Press]]|isbn=9780193862142|pages=[https://archive.org/details/bachorgelbuchlei0000stin/page/2 2\u20139]|doi=10.1093/acprof:oso/9780193862142.001.0001}}\n*{{citation|title=J.S. Bach's Great Eighteen Organ Chorales|first=Russell|last= Stinson|publisher=[[Oxford University Press]]|year= 2001|isbn=0-19-516556-X|url=http://www.oxfordscholarship.com/view/10.1093/acprof:oso/9780195116663.001.0001/acprof-9780195116663-chapter-4|pages=78\u201380|doi=10.1093/acprof:oso/9780195116663.001.0001}}\n*{{citation|title=J. S. Bach at His Royal Instrument: Essays on His Organ Works|first=Russel|last=Stinson|publisher=[[Oxford University Press]]|year= 2012|page=16|isbn=978-0199917235}}\n*{{citation|first=Charles Sanford|last=Terry|authorlink=Charles Sanford Terry (historian)|title= Bach's Chorals, vol. III|year=1921| url=https://archive.org/stream/bachschorals03terr#page/100/mode/2up|pages=101\u2013104|publisher=Cambridge, The University Press}}\n*{{citation|title=The Routledge Research Companion to Johann Sebastian Bach|editor-first=Robin A. |editor-last=Leaver|publisher=Taylor & Francis| year=2017|isbn=9781409417903|chapter=Manuscripts|first=Yo|last=Tomita|pages=47\u201388}}\n*{{citation|title=The Singing of the Strasbourg Protestants, 1523-1541|series=St Andrews Studies in Reformation History|first=Daniel|last= Trocm\u00e9-Latter|publisher=Ashgate|year= 2015|isbn=9781472432063}}\n*{{citation|title=Histories of Heinrich Sch\u00fctz|first=Bettina|last= Varwig|publisher=[[Cambridge University Press]]|year= 2011|isbn=978-1139502016}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Wachowski |first1=Gerd |author-link1=:de:Gerd Wachowski |date=1983 |chapter=Die vierstimmigen Chor\u00e4le Johann Sebastian Bachs: Untersuchungen zu den Druckausgaben von 1765 bis 1932 und zur Frage der Authentizit\u00e4t |trans-chapter=The four-part chorales of Johann Sebastian Bach: research into the printed editions from 1765 to 1732 and regarding the question of authenticity |chapter-url=https://journals.qucosa.de/ejournals/bjb/article/view/2434 |editor1-last=Schulze |editor1-first=Hans-Joachim |editor1-link=Hans-Joachim Schulze |editor2-last=Wolff |editor2-first=Christoph |editor2-link=Christoph Wolff |title=Bach-Jahrbuch 1983 |trans-title=Bach Yearbook 1983 |url=https://journals.qucosa.de/ejournals/bjb/issue/view/145 |series=[[Bach-Jahrbuch]] |language=de |volume=69 |others=[[Neue Bachgesellschaft]] |location=Berlin |publisher={{ill|Evangelische Verlagsanstalt|de}} |pages=51\u201379 |doi=10.13141/bjb.v1983 |isbn= |issn=0084-7682 |ref=harv }}\n*{{citation|title=Wer ist wer im Gesangbuch?|language=de|series=Handbuch Zum Evangelischen Gesangbuch|volume=2|editor-first=Wolfgang|editor-last=Herbst|publisher=Vandenhoeck & Ruprecht|year= 2001|isbn=3525503237|chapter=Wolfgang Dachstein|first=\u00c9dith|last=Weber|pages=70\u201371}}\n*{{citation |last1=Werner |first1=Wilfried |date=2016 |chapter='Nicht mitzuhassen, mitzulieben bin ich da!' Exegese und Predigt zu Psalm 137|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=adxtDQAAQBAJ&pg=PA197 |editor1-last=Hartlapp |editor1-first=Johannes |editor2-last=Cramer |editor2-first=Andrea |title=\"Und was ich noch sagen wollte ...\": Festschrift f\u00fcr Wolfgang Kabus zum 80. Geburtstag |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=adxtDQAAQBAJ |language=de |publisher=Frank & Timme |pages=193\u2013216 |isbn=978-3732903139}}\n*{{citation|first=Peter|last=Williams|title=The Organ Music of J.S. Bach, Volume II: BWV 599\u2013771, etc.| series=Cambridge Studies in Music|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=1980|isbn=0-521-31700-2}}\n*{{citation|first=Peter|last=Williams|title=The Organ Music of J. S. Bach|edition=2nd|publisher=[[Cambridge University Press]]|year=2003|isbn=0-521-89115-9}}\n*{{citation|title=Bach: A Musical Biography|first=Peter|last= Williams|publisher=[[Cambridge University Press]]|year= 2016|isbn=978-1107139251}}\n*{{citation|title=J.S. Bach as Organist|year=1986|publisher=[[Indiana University Press]]|editor=George Stauffer|editor2=Ernest May|chapter=Johann Adam Reinken and Johann Sebastian Bach: On the Context of Bach's Early Works| first=Christoph|last=Wolff|pages=57\u201380|isbn= 0713452625}}\n*{{citation|last=Yearsley|first=David|title=Bach Discoveries|year=2009|journal=[[Early Music]]|pages=489\u2013492|volume=37|issue=3|doi=10.1093/em/cap055}}\n*{{citation|title=Bach's Feet: The Organ Pedals in European Culture|first=David |last=Yearsley|publisher=[[Cambridge University Press]]|year= 2012|isbn=978-1139500111|pages=94\u201397}}\n* {{citation |last1=Zahn |first1=Johannes |author-link1=Johannes Zahn |date=1891 |chapter=7663 |chapter-url=https://archive.org/stream/1508286757bsb11304502#page/n513/mode/2up |title=Die Melodien der deutschen evangelischen Kirchenlieder |volume=[https://archive.org/details/1508286757bsb11304502 IV] |location=G\u00fctersloh |publisher=[[Bertelsmann]] |language=de |pages=508\u2013509 |title-link=scores:Die Melodien der deutschen evangelischen Kirchenlieder (Zahn, Johannes) }}\n* {{citation |last1=Zahn |first1=Johannes |author-link1=Johannes Zahn |date=1893|title=Die Melodien der deutschen evangelischen Kirchenlieder |volume=[https://archive.org/details/1508288358bsb11304504 VI] |location=G\u00fctersloh |publisher=[[Bertelsmann]] |language=de |title-link=scores:Die Melodien der deutschen evangelischen Kirchenlieder (Zahn, Johannes) }}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commonscat}}\n* {{IMSLP|work=An Wasserfl\u00fcssen Babylon (Schein, Johann Hermann)|cname =An Wasserfl\u00fcssen Babylon, Opella nova (Geistliche Konzerte, Leipzig, 1618) by Johann Hermann Schein}}\n* {{IMSLP|work= Becker Psalter, Op.5 (Sch\u00fctz, Heinrich)|cname =An Wasserfl\u00fcssen Babylon, Becker Psalter, Op.5 (Psalmen Davids, Freiberg, 1628) by\nHeinrich Sch\u00fctz}}\n* {{IMSLP|work=An Wasserfl\u00fcssen Babylon, P.17 (Pachelbel, Johann)|cname =An Wasserfl\u00fcssen Babylon, P.17 |work2=An Wasserfl\u00fcssen Babylon, P.18 (Pachelbel, Johann)|cname2=An Wasserfl\u00fcssen Babylon, P.18|work3=An Wasserfl\u00fcssen Babylon, P.20 (Pachelbel, Johann)|cname3=An Wasserfl\u00fcssen Babylon, P.20 by Johann Pachelbel}}\n* {{IMSLP|work=Complete Organ Works (Reincken, Johann Adam)|cname=An Wasserfl\u00fcssen Babylon (Complete Organ Works, ed. Klaus Beckmann, Breitkopf & H\u00e4rtel, 1974) by Johann Adam Reincken}}\n* {{IMSLP|work=An Wasserfl\u00fcssen Babylon, BWV 267 (Bach, Johann Sebastian)|cname =An Wasserfl\u00fcssen Babylon, BWV 267|work2=An Wasserfl\u00fcssen Babylon, BWV 653 (Bach, Johann Sebastian)|cname2=BWV 653, by Johann Sebastian Bach}}\n* [http://colmarisches.free.fr/Choralmelodien/Chorals/AnWasserflussen.html Zu Fassungen der Melodie in Els\u00e4ssischen Gesangb\u00fcchern] colmarisches.free.fr\n* [https://www.dzb.de/index.php?site_id=2.1.3.3&id=3280&show=titles Glebe, Karl ; Heinermann, Otto: / Vorspiele zum deutsch-evangelischen Gesangbuch f\u00fcr Orgel] dzb.de\n* G. W. Fink: [https://books.google.de/books?id=wuMqAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA38 No. 24] Allgemeine musikalische Zeitung, Volume 38, 1836\n* {{cite web| url = http://www.thescrollensemble.com/en/programme-notes-an-wasserflussen-babylon/| title = An Wasserfl\u00fcssen Babylons|publisher = The Scroll Ensemble| accessdate = 3 March 2018}}\n*{{cite web| url= http://www.bach-chorales.com/ |title= The Four-Part Chorales of J.S. Bach|access-date=9 April 2018|first=Luke|last=Dahn}}\n\n{{Hymns and songs based on Psalms}}\n{{German Lutheran hymns}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:An Wasserflussen Babylon}}\n[[Category:Psalm settings]]\n[[Category:Lutheran hymns based on Psalms]]\n", "name_user": "Nigel Ish", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eOrgan settings:remove surplus *", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/An_Wasserfl%C3%BCssen_Babylon"}
{"title_page": "Blarney Stone", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=October 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}}\n[[File:The Blarney Stone.jpg|thumb|The Blarney Stone]]\nThe '''Blarney Stone''' ({{lang-ga|Cloch na Blarnan}}) is a block of [[Carboniferous limestone]]<ref name=\"guardian\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/mar/16/mystery-blarney-stone-heritage-solved|title=Mystery of Blarney Stone's heritage finally solved|date=16 March 2014|accessdate=16 March 2014|publisher=The Guardian}}</ref> built into the [[battlement]]s of [[Blarney Castle]], [[Blarney]], about {{convert|8|km|mi|0|abbr=off}} from [[Cork (city)|Cork]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]. According to legend, kissing the stone endows the kisser with ''the [[wikt:gift of the gab|gift of the gab]]'' (great [[eloquence]] or skill at [[flattery]]). The stone was set into a tower of the castle in 1446. The castle is a popular tourist site in Ireland, attracting visitors from all over the world to kiss the stone and tour the castle and its gardens.\n\nThe word ''[[wikt:blarney|blarney]]'' has come to mean \"clever, flattering, or coaxing talk\". Irish politician [[John O'Connor Power]] defined it this way: \"Blarney is something more than mere flattery. It is flattery sweetened by humour and flavoured by wit. Those who mix with Irish folk have many examples of it in their everyday experience.\"<ref>'Irish Wit and Humour', John O'Connor Power, Time, 1890, p. 178.</ref> [[Letitia Elizabeth Landon]] described its contemporary meaning in an article entitled 'Blarney Castle' in 1832\n\n==Origins==\n[[File:Blarney Stone from below.jpg|thumb|View of the Blarney Stone from the ground]]\nA number of stories attempt to explain the origin of the stone and surrounding legend. An early story involves the goddess [[Cl\u00edodhna]].<ref>James MacKillop, ''A Dictionary of Celtic Mythology''. Oxford. pp. 43\u201344, 91</ref><ref>Patricia Monaghan, ''The Encyclopedia of Celtic Mythology and Folklore''. New York: Facts On File. 2004. pp. 48, 91</ref> Cormac Laidir McCarthy, the builder of Blarney Castle,<ref>[http://www.libraryireland.com/Pedigrees1/MacCarthyMuskry.php Irish Pedigrees: MacCarthy, Lords of Muskry] #119</ref> being involved in a lawsuit in the 15th century, appealed to Cl\u00edodhna for her assistance. She told McCarthy to kiss the first stone he found in the morning on his way to court, and he did so, with the result that he pleaded his case with great eloquence and won. Thus the Blarney Stone is said to impart \"the ability to deceive without offending\". MacCarthy then incorporated it into the [[parapet]] of the castle.<ref>Richard Marsh, Elan Penn, Frank McCourt, ''The Legends & Lands of Ireland''. Penn Publishing. pp. 107\u2013110</ref>\n\nThe proprietors of Blarney Castle list several other explanations of the origins of the stone on their website.<ref name=BlarneyCastle>{{cite web |url=http://www.blarneycastle.ie/pages/stone |title=The Blarney Stone |work=Blarney Castle website |accessdate=11 July 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100830230658/http://www.blarneycastle.ie/pages/stone |archivedate=30 August 2010 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Many of these suppose that the stone had previously been in Ireland, was taken to Scotland and then returned to Ireland in 1314.<ref name=BlarneyCastle/> The stories listed include one suggesting that the stone was presented to Cormac McCarthy by [[Robert the Bruce]] in 1314 in recognition of his support in the [[Battle of Bannockburn]].<ref name=BlarneyCastle/> This legend holds that this was a piece of the [[Stone of Scone]] and was installed at McCarthy's castle of Blarney.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Castleden |first1=Rodney |title=Castles of the celtic lands: the historic castles of Ireland, Scotland and Wales |year=2006 |publisher=Barnes & Noble |isbn=0-7607-7937-6 |page=26}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Varner |first1=Gary R. |title=Menhirs, dolmen, and circles of stone: the folklore and magic of sacred stone |year=2004 |publisher=Algora Publishing |isbn=0-87586-349-3 |page=61}}</ref> Although colourful, this folk legend does not account for the fact that it supposes that the stone was removed from Scotland 18 years before Bannockburn. Moreover, analysis by geologists at the University of Glasgow in 2014 found the stone's geochemical signature matches local limestone.<ref name=\"guardian\"/>\n\n==Ritual==\n[[Filekiinalaisen suomalaisen pussaus.jpg|thumb|Person kissing the Blarney Stone]]\nThe ritual of kissing the Blarney Stone, according to the castle's proprietors, has been performed by \"millions of people\", including \"world statesmen, literary giants [and] legends of the [[silver screen]]\".<ref name=BlarneyCastle/> The kiss, however, is not casually achieved. To touch the stone with one's lips, the participant must ascend to the castle's peak, then lean over backwards on the parapet's edge. This is traditionally achieved with the help of an assistant. Although the parapet is now fitted with [[wrought-iron]] guide rails and protective crossbars, the ritual can still trigger attacks of [[acrophobia]], an extreme or irrational fear of heights.\n\n[[File:Kissing the Blarney Stone 1897.jpg|thumb|Kissing the stone in 1897, before the safeguards were installed.]]\nBefore the safeguards were installed, the kiss was performed with real risk to life and limb, as participants were grasped by the ankles and dangled bodily from the height.<ref name=\"world and its people\">{{cite book |last=Dunton |first=Larkin |title=The World and Its People |url=https://archive.org/details/worldanditspeop05duntgoog |publisher=Silver, Burdett |year=1896 |page=[https://archive.org/details/worldanditspeop05duntgoog/page/n42 84]}}</ref> In the [[Sherlock Holmes]] radio dramatisation \"The Adventure of the Blarney Stone\" (first broadcast on 18 March 1946), a man attempting to kiss the Blarney Stone falls to his death. Holmes' investigation reveals this as a murder, the man's boots having been surreptitiously greased before the attempt.\n\n[[William Henry Hurlbert]] wrote in 1888 that the legend of the stone seemed to be less than a hundred years old at that time, suggesting the tradition began late in the 18th century.<ref>{{cite book |title=Ireland Under Coercion: The Diary of an American |first=William Henry |last=Hurlbert |publisher=Houghton Mifflin |year=1888 |edition=2nd |page=[https://archive.org/details/irelandundercoe02hurlgoog/page/n262 232] |url=https://archive.org/details/irelandundercoe02hurlgoog}}</ref> The legend of the Blarney Stone was described in ''A classical dictionary of the vulgar tongue'' by Francis Grose, printed 1785.<ref>{{cite book|author=Grose, Francis|title=A Classical Dictionary of the Vulgar Tongue|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zLAJs0_prpwC&pg=PT29&dq=%22blarney+stone%22|accessdate=23 December 2010|year=1785|publisher=S. Hooper|location=London|page=29}}</ref>\n\n==Legend==\nIt is claimed that the synonymy of \"blarney\" with \"empty flattery\" or \"beguiling talk\" derives from one of two sources. One story involves the goddess Cl\u00edodhna and Cormac Laidir MacCarthy (see \"Origins\" above). Another legend suggests that [[Elizabeth I of England|Queen Elizabeth I]] requested Cormac Teige McCarthy, the Lord of Blarney, be deprived of his traditional land rights. Cormac travelled to see the queen, but was certain he would not persuade her to change her mind as he wasn't an effective speaker. He met an old woman on the way who told him that anyone who kissed a particular stone in Blarney Castle would be given the gift of eloquent speech. Cormac went on to persuade the queen that he should not be deprived of his land.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.irishindeed.com/page.htm?pg=BLARNEY%20STONE|title=Irish Blessings - Legend of the Blarney Stone}}</ref>\n\n{{Quote box\n|quote=\n'Tis there's the stone that whoever kisses\n\nHe never misses to grow eloquent;\n\n'Tis he may clamber to a lady's chamber,\n\nOr become a member of Parliament.\n\n\"A noble spouter he'll sure turn out, or\n\nAn out and outer to be let alone;\n\nDon't try to hinder him, or to bewilder him,\n\nFor he is a pilgrim from the Blarney stone.\" |source=[[Francis Sylvester Mahony]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.blarneycastle.ie/stories |title=Fun stories |work=Blarney Castle website |accessdate=11 July 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080721003742/http://www.blarneycastle.ie/stories |archivedate=21 July 2008 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> |width=20% |align=right}}\n\nEchoing the supposed power of the stone, an Irish bard of the early 19th century, [[Francis Sylvester Mahony]], added a number of (humorous) lines to Richard Alfred Millikin's \"''The Groves of Blarney''\" (right).\n\nAccording to [[Texas Tech University traditions|tradition at Texas Tech University]], a stone fragment on display since 1939 outside the old Electrical Engineering Building is a missing piece of the Blarney Stone.<ref>{{cite news |first=Cindy |last=Martin |title=The Blarney Stone...at Texas Tech? |url=http://www.swco.ttu.edu/University_Archive/pdf/1987.pdf |format=pdf |work=Texas Techsan |publisher=Texas Tech Alumni Association |location=Lubbock, Texas |page=25 |date=March\u2013April 1987}}, also cited in<br>{{cite web |url=http://www.ttu.edu/traditions/blarney.php |title=Blarney Stone |work=Texas Tech University |accessdate=10 July 2008}}</ref> How this was determined is unknown.<ref>{{Cite journal|first=Jennifer |last=Ritz |url=http://www.depts.ttu.edu/centerforcampuslife/traditions/Traditions.pdf |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140725111915/http://www.depts.ttu.edu/centerforcampuslife/traditions/Traditions.pdf |archive-date=2014-07-25 |format=pdf |title= This is Texas Tech |work=Texas Techsan Magazine |publisher=Texas Tech Alumni Association |page=7 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Song==\nThe [[Irish traditional music|traditional Irish]] song \"''The Blarney Stone''\" ([[Roud Folk Song Index|Roud]] 4800) has been recorded by artists including [[Tom Lenihan]], [[Margaret Barry]] and [[Bob Davenport (singer)|Bob Davenport]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.clarelibrary.ie/eolas/coclare/songs/cmc/the_blarney_stone_tlenihan.htm|title=Clare County Library: Songs of Clare - The Blarney Stone sung by Tom Lenihan|website=www.clarelibrary.ie|accessdate=27 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/tracks/n2hx96|title=The Blarney Stone - Margaret Barry Song - BBC Music|website=BBC|accessdate=27 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=YGdQDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA199|title=The British Folk Revival: 1944\u20132002|first=Michael|last=Brocken|date=29 September 2017|publisher=Routledge|accessdate=27 February 2019|via=Google Books}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{wikisource|Letitia Elizabeth Landon (L. E. L.) in Fisher's Drawing Room Scrap Book, 1832/Blarney Castle|Blarney Castle, by L. E. L.}}\n*[[Answering Stone]]\n*[[Kiss me, I'm Irish]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite book |title=Blarney Castle: Its History, Development and Purpose |first=Mark |last=Samuel |author2=Hamlyn, Kate |publisher=[[Cork University Press|Cork University]] |year=2007 |isbn=978-1-85918-411-0}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.blarneycastle.ie/ Blarney Castle & Gardens: The Home of the Blarney Stone]\n* [http://www.strollingguides.co.uk/books/cork/places/blarney.php Photos and Description]\n{{Coord|51.929091|N|8.570564|W|display=title}}\n{{Mac C\u00e1rthaigh}}\n{{Superstitions}}\n\n[[Category:Stones]]\n[[Category:Cl\u00edodhna]]\n[[Category:Irish folklore]]\n[[Category:Limestone]]\n[[Category:MacCarthy dynasty]]\n[[Category:Superstitions of Europe]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in County Cork]]\n[[Category:Individual rocks]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=October 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}}\n[[File:The Blarney Stone.jpg|thumb|The Blarney Stone]]\nThe '''Blarney Stone''' ({{lang-ga|Cloch na Blarnan}}) is a block of [[Carboniferous limestone]]<ref name=\"guardian\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/mar/16/mystery-blarney-stone-heritage-solved|title=Mystery of Blarney Stone's heritage finally solved|date=16 March 2014|accessdate=16 March 2014|publisher=The Guardian}}</ref> built into the [[battlement]]s of [[Blarney Castle]], [[Blarney]], about {{convert|8|km|mi|0|abbr=off}} from [[Cork (city)|Cork]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]. According to legend, kissing the stone endows the kisser with ''the [[wikt:gift of the gab|gift of the gab]]'' (great [[eloquence]] or skill at [[flattery]]). The stone was set into a tower of the castle in 1446. The castle is a popular tourist site in Ireland, attracting visitors from all over the world to kiss the stone and tour the castle and its gardens.\n\nThe word ''[[wikt:blarney|blarney]]'' has come to mean \"clever, flattering, or coaxing talk\". Irish politician [[John O'Connor Power]] defined it this way: \"Blarney is something more than mere flattery. It is flattery sweetened by humour and flavoured by wit. Those who mix with Irish folk have many examples of it in their everyday experience.\"<ref>'Irish Wit and Humour', John O'Connor Power, Time, 1890, p. 178.</ref> [[Letitia Elizabeth Landon]] described its contemporary meaning in an article entitled 'Blarney Castle' in 1832\n\n==Origins==\n[[File:Blarney Stone from below.jpg|thumb|View of the Blarney Stone from the ground]]\nA number of stories attempt to explain the origin of the stone and surrounding legend. An early story involves the goddess [[Cl\u00edodhna]].<ref>James MacKillop, ''A Dictionary of Celtic Mythology''. Oxford. pp. 43\u201344, 91</ref><ref>Patricia Monaghan, ''The Encyclopedia of Celtic Mythology and Folklore''. New York: Facts On File. 2004. pp. 48, 91</ref> Cormac Laidir McCarthy, the builder of Blarney Castle,<ref>[http://www.libraryireland.com/Pedigrees1/MacCarthyMuskry.php Irish Pedigrees: MacCarthy, Lords of Muskry] #119</ref> being involved in a lawsuit in the 15th century, appealed to Cl\u00edodhna for her assistance. She told McCarthy to kiss the first stone he found in the morning on his way to court, and he did so, with the result that he pleaded his case with great eloquence and won. Thus the Blarney Stone is said to impart \"the ability to deceive without offending\". MacCarthy then incorporated it into the [[parapet]] of the castle.<ref>Richard Marsh, Elan Penn, Frank McCourt, ''The Legends & Lands of Ireland''. Penn Publishing. pp. 107\u2013110</ref>\n\nThe proprietors of Blarney Castle list several other explanations of the origins of the stone on their website.<ref name=BlarneyCastle>{{cite web |url=http://www.blarneycastle.ie/pages/stone |title=The Blarney Stone |work=Blarney Castle website |accessdate=11 July 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100830230658/http://www.blarneycastle.ie/pages/stone |archivedate=30 August 2010 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Many of these suppose that the stone had previously been in Ireland, was taken to Scotland and then returned to Ireland in 1314.<ref name=BlarneyCastle/> The stories listed include one suggesting that the stone was presented to Cormac McCarthy by [[Robert the Bruce]] in 1314 in recognition of his support in the [[Battle of Bannockburn]].<ref name=BlarneyCastle/> This legend holds that this was a piece of the [[Stone of Scone]] and was installed at McCarthy's castle of Blarney.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Castleden |first1=Rodney |title=Castles of the celtic lands: the historic castles of Ireland, Scotland and Wales |year=2006 |publisher=Barnes & Noble |isbn=0-7607-7937-6 |page=26}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Varner |first1=Gary R. |title=Menhirs, dolmen, and circles of stone: the folklore and magic of sacred stone |year=2004 |publisher=Algora Publishing |isbn=0-87586-349-3 |page=61}}</ref> Although colourful, this folk legend does not account for the fact that it supposes that the stone was removed from Scotland 18 years before Bannockburn. Moreover, analysis by geologists at the University of Glasgow in 2014 found the stone's geochemical signature matches local limestone.<ref name=\"guardian\"/>\n\n==Ritual==\n[[File:Kiss the Blarney Stone.jpg|thumb|Person kissing the Blarney Stone]]\nThe ritual of kissing the Blarney Stone, according to the castle's proprietors, has been performed by \"millions of people\", including \"world statesmen, literary giants [and] legends of the [[silver screen]]\".<ref name=BlarneyCastle/> The kiss, however, is not casually achieved. To touch the stone with one's lips, the participant must ascend to the castle's peak, then lean over backwards on the parapet's edge. This is traditionally achieved with the help of an assistant. Although the parapet is now fitted with [[wrought-iron]] guide rails and protective crossbars, the ritual can still trigger attacks of [[acrophobia]], an extreme or irrational fear of heights.\n\n[[File:Kissing the Blarney Stone 1897.jpg|thumb|Kissing the stone in 1897, before the safeguards were installed.]]\nBefore the safeguards were installed, the kiss was performed with real risk to life and limb, as participants were grasped by the ankles and dangled bodily from the height.<ref name=\"world and its people\">{{cite book |last=Dunton |first=Larkin |title=The World and Its People |url=https://archive.org/details/worldanditspeop05duntgoog |publisher=Silver, Burdett |year=1896 |page=[https://archive.org/details/worldanditspeop05duntgoog/page/n42 84]}}</ref> In the [[Sherlock Holmes]] radio dramatisation \"The Adventure of the Blarney Stone\" (first broadcast on 18 March 1946), a man attempting to kiss the Blarney Stone falls to his death. Holmes' investigation reveals this as a murder, the man's boots having been surreptitiously greased before the attempt.\n\n[[William Henry Hurlbert]] wrote in 1888 that the legend of the stone seemed to be less than a hundred years old at that time, suggesting the tradition began late in the 18th century.<ref>{{cite book |title=Ireland Under Coercion: The Diary of an American |first=William Henry |last=Hurlbert |publisher=Houghton Mifflin |year=1888 |edition=2nd |page=[https://archive.org/details/irelandundercoe02hurlgoog/page/n262 232] |url=https://archive.org/details/irelandundercoe02hurlgoog}}</ref> The legend of the Blarney Stone was described in ''A classical dictionary of the vulgar tongue'' by Francis Grose, printed 1785.<ref>{{cite book|author=Grose, Francis|title=A Classical Dictionary of the Vulgar Tongue|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zLAJs0_prpwC&pg=PT29&dq=%22blarney+stone%22|accessdate=23 December 2010|year=1785|publisher=S. Hooper|location=London|page=29}}</ref>\n\n==Legend==\nIt is claimed that the synonymy of \"blarney\" with \"empty flattery\" or \"beguiling talk\" derives from one of two sources. One story involves the goddess Cl\u00edodhna and Cormac Laidir MacCarthy (see \"Origins\" above). Another legend suggests that [[Elizabeth I of England|Queen Elizabeth I]] requested Cormac Teige McCarthy, the Lord of Blarney, be deprived of his traditional land rights. Cormac travelled to see the queen, but was certain he would not persuade her to change her mind as he wasn't an effective speaker. He met an old woman on the way who told him that anyone who kissed a particular stone in Blarney Castle would be given the gift of eloquent speech. Cormac went on to persuade the queen that he should not be deprived of his land.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.irishindeed.com/page.htm?pg=BLARNEY%20STONE|title=Irish Blessings - Legend of the Blarney Stone}}</ref>\n\n{{Quote box\n|quote=\n'Tis there's the stone that whoever kisses\n\nHe never misses to grow eloquent;\n\n'Tis he may clamber to a lady's chamber,\n\nOr become a member of Parliament.\n\n\"A noble spouter he'll sure turn out, or\n\nAn out and outer to be let alone;\n\nDon't try to hinder him, or to bewilder him,\n\nFor he is a pilgrim from the Blarney stone.\" |source=[[Francis Sylvester Mahony]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.blarneycastle.ie/stories |title=Fun stories |work=Blarney Castle website |accessdate=11 July 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080721003742/http://www.blarneycastle.ie/stories |archivedate=21 July 2008 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> |width=20% |align=right}}\n\nEchoing the supposed power of the stone, an Irish bard of the early 19th century, [[Francis Sylvester Mahony]], added a number of (humorous) lines to Richard Alfred Millikin's \"''The Groves of Blarney''\" (right).\n\nAccording to [[Texas Tech University traditions|tradition at Texas Tech University]], a stone fragment on display since 1939 outside the old Electrical Engineering Building is a missing piece of the Blarney Stone.<ref>{{cite news |first=Cindy |last=Martin |title=The Blarney Stone...at Texas Tech? |url=http://www.swco.ttu.edu/University_Archive/pdf/1987.pdf |format=pdf |work=Texas Techsan |publisher=Texas Tech Alumni Association |location=Lubbock, Texas |page=25 |date=March\u2013April 1987}}, also cited in<br>{{cite web |url=http://www.ttu.edu/traditions/blarney.php |title=Blarney Stone |work=Texas Tech University |accessdate=10 July 2008}}</ref> How this was determined is unknown.<ref>{{Cite journal|first=Jennifer |last=Ritz |url=http://www.depts.ttu.edu/centerforcampuslife/traditions/Traditions.pdf |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140725111915/http://www.depts.ttu.edu/centerforcampuslife/traditions/Traditions.pdf |archive-date=2014-07-25 |format=pdf |title= This is Texas Tech |work=Texas Techsan Magazine |publisher=Texas Tech Alumni Association |page=7 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Song==\nThe [[Irish traditional music|traditional Irish]] song \"''The Blarney Stone''\" ([[Roud Folk Song Index|Roud]] 4800) has been recorded by artists including [[Tom Lenihan]], [[Margaret Barry]] and [[Bob Davenport (singer)|Bob Davenport]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.clarelibrary.ie/eolas/coclare/songs/cmc/the_blarney_stone_tlenihan.htm|title=Clare County Library: Songs of Clare - The Blarney Stone sung by Tom Lenihan|website=www.clarelibrary.ie|accessdate=27 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/tracks/n2hx96|title=The Blarney Stone - Margaret Barry Song - BBC Music|website=BBC|accessdate=27 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=YGdQDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA199|title=The British Folk Revival: 1944\u20132002|first=Michael|last=Brocken|date=29 September 2017|publisher=Routledge|accessdate=27 February 2019|via=Google Books}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{wikisource|Letitia Elizabeth Landon (L. E. L.) in Fisher's Drawing Room Scrap Book, 1832/Blarney Castle|Blarney Castle, by L. E. L.}}\n*[[Answering Stone]]\n*[[Kiss me, I'm Irish]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite book |title=Blarney Castle: Its History, Development and Purpose |first=Mark |last=Samuel |author2=Hamlyn, Kate |publisher=[[Cork University Press|Cork University]] |year=2007 |isbn=978-1-85918-411-0}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.blarneycastle.ie/ Blarney Castle & Gardens: The Home of the Blarney Stone]\n* [http://www.strollingguides.co.uk/books/cork/places/blarney.php Photos and Description]\n{{Coord|51.929091|N|8.570564|W|display=title}}\n{{Mac C\u00e1rthaigh}}\n{{Superstitions}}\n\n[[Category:Stones]]\n[[Category:Cl\u00edodhna]]\n[[Category:Irish folklore]]\n[[Category:Limestone]]\n[[Category:MacCarthy dynasty]]\n[[Category:Superstitions of Europe]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in County Cork]]\n[[Category:Individual rocks]]\n", "name_user": "2001:999:42:1a06:876:e1e8:fdda:d5f3", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eRitual)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blarney_Stone"}
{"title_page": "Lydia Benecke", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|German criminal psychologist}}\n{{Infobox writer\n| embed            =\n| honorific_prefix =\n| name             = Lydia Benecke\n| honorific_suffix =\n| image            = LydiaBenecke.jpg\n| image_size       =\n| image_upright    =\n| alt              =\n| caption          = Lydia Benecke, 2017\n| native_name      =\n| native_name_lang =\n| pseudonym        =\n| birth_name       = E. C. Wawrzyniak\n| birth_date       = <!-- {{Birth date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| birth_place      = [[Bytom]], Poland\n| death_place      =\n| resting_place    =\n| occupation       =Criminal psychologist and writer\n| language         =\n| residence        =[[Cologne]] Germany\n| nationality      =\n| citizenship      = German\n| education        =Psychology\n| alma_mater       =\n| home_town        =\n| period           =\n| genre            = Popular science non-fiction.\n| subject          = <!-- or: | subjects = -->\n| movement         =\n| notableworks     = <!-- or: | notablework = -->\n| spouse           = <!-- or: | spouses = -->\n| partner          = <!-- or: | partners = -->\n| children         =\n| relatives        =\n| awards           =\n| signature        =\n| signature_alt    =\n| years_active     =\n| module           =\n| website          = <!-- {{URL|example.org}} -->\n| portaldisp       = <!-- \"on\", \"yes\", \"true\", etc.; or omit -->\n}}\n\n'''Lydia Benecke''' (born in 1982 as ''E. C. Wawrzyniak''<ref>{{cite web |last1=Benecke |first1=Lydia |title=Ist das Pers\u00f6nlichkeitskonstrukt \"Experience Seeking\"bei Sadomasochisten st\u00e4rker ausgepr\u00e4gtals bei Nicht-Sadomasochisten? |url=http://benecke-psychology.com/files/DIPLOMARBEIT_LYDIA_BENECKE_GEB_WAWRZYNIAK.PDF |website=Benecke Psychology |publisher=Diplomarbeit Ruhr-Universit\u00e4t Bochum |accessdate=17 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190218021518/http://benecke-psychology.com/files/DIPLOMARBEIT_LYDIA_BENECKE_GEB_WAWRZYNIAK.PDF |archive-date=18 February 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> in [[Bytom]], [[Poland]]) is a German criminal psychologist and writer of popular science non-fiction.\n\n==Life==\n\nBenecke was born in [[Poland]] and left for Germany at the age of 4 with her mother. She grew up in [[Bottrop]] and developed her interest in criminal cases from a young age.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hildebrand-Schute |first1=Ute |title=Kriminalpsychologin sammelte schon als Kind Kriminalf\u00e4lle |url=https://www.waz.de/staedte/bottrop/kriminalpsychologin-sammelte-schon-als-kind-kriminalfaelle-id215493627.html |publisher=WAZ |accessdate=15 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190216035357/https://www.waz.de/staedte/bottrop/kriminalpsychologin-sammelte-schon-als-kind-kriminalfaelle-id215493627.html |archive-date=16 February 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> After finishing school at the [[Janusz-Korczak-Gesamtschule (Bottrop)|Janusz-Korczak-Gesamtschule]] in [[Bottrop]], she studied Psychology, [[Psychopathology]] and [[Forensic science]] at the [[Ruhr University Bochum]].<ref name=\"Stalker\">[http://www.sat1.de/tv/stalker-auf-frischer-tat-ertappt/die-experten/lydia-benecke-diplom-psychologin Lydia Benecke, Diplom-Psychologin.] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190216035309/https://www.sat1.de/tv/stalker-auf-frischer-tat-ertappt/die-experten/lydia-benecke-diplom-psychologin |date=16 February 2019 }} Homepage of [[Sat.1]].</ref> She was married to [[Mark Benecke]]. She lives in [[Cologne]] and is active in the German skeptical organization [[Gesellschaft zur wissenschaftlichen Untersuchung von Parawissenschaften|GWUP]].\n\n==Career==\n\n===Psychologist===\n\nBenecke attended an adult education course in psychology as a teenager. After a school internship she worked as a freelancer for a psychological psychotherapist during her extracurricular time.\n\nSince 2008 she has been working therapeutically in a social therapy institution with sexual and violent offenders <ref>{{cite web|title=Ist das Pers\u00f6nlichkeitskonstrukt \"Experience Seeking\" bei Sadomasochisten st\u00e4rker ausgepr\u00e4gt als bei Nicht-Sadomasochisten? Eine Betrachtung des Experience Seeking und andere psychologische Faktoren bei inklinierenden Sadomasochisten|periodical=Benecke.com|url=http://benecke.com/pdf/DIPLOMARBEIT_LYDIA_BENECKE_GEB_WAWRZYNIAK.PDF|url-status=dead|format=PDF; 1,08&nbsp;MB|accessdate=26 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130320012040/http://benecke.com/pdf/DIPLOMARBEIT_LYDIA_BENECKE_GEB_WAWRZYNIAK.PDF|archivedate=20 March 2013|last=Lydia Benecke}}</ref>\n\nBetween 2009 and 2013 she worked as a psychological consultant in criminal cases and in public relations for her then husband's company, the criminal biologist Mark Benecke<ref name=\"Jugendschutzbeauftragte\">[http://www.smjg.org/ueber-uns/personen/lydia-jugendschutzbeauftragte/ Lydia Benecke stellt sich selbst vor.] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190216094152/https://www.smjg.org/ueber-uns/personen/lydia-jugendschutzbeauftragte/ |date=16 February 2019 }} Homepage der SMJG.</ref><ref name=\"Bericht Focus\">[http://www.focus.de/wissen/mensch/tid-24277/kriminalbiologe-mark-benecke-die-schraegen-faelle-des-dr-tod_aid_687597.html Stefanie Reiffert: ''Kriminalbiologe Mark Benecke. Die schr\u00e4gen F\u00e4lle des \u201eDr. Tod\u201c''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190216040807/https://www.focus.de/wissen/mensch/tid-24277/kriminalbiologe-mark-benecke-die-schraegen-faelle-des-dr-tod_aid_687597.html |date=16 February 2019 }} Artikel auf der Homepage des [[Focus (German magazine)|Focus]].</ref> Nowadays, she works as an independent criminal psychologist with an office in Cologne in the fields of consulting and education. Her main areas of work are [[paraphilia]], [[personality disorders]] (especially psychopathy, dissocial personality disorders and borderline personality disorders), [[Psychological trauma]], superstitious beliefs, subcultures (especially BDSM scene, [[Dark culture]], [[Goth subculture]], sects and [[vampire subculture]].<ref name=\"Ein Psychopath liebt sein Kind nicht mehr als sein Auto\">[http://www.t-online.de/nachrichten/specials/id_66699686/so-ticken-psychopathen-eine-psychologin-erklaert.html Ruth Friedrich: ''T\u00e4ter ohne Reue im Kopf. \u201eEin Psychopath liebt sein Kind nicht mehr als sein Auto\u201c''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180330061436/http://www.t-online.de/nachrichten/specials/id_66699686/so-ticken-psychopathen-eine-psychologin-erklaert.html |date=30 March 2018 }} Interview mit Lydia Benecke auf der Homepage von [[T-Online]].</ref>\n\n=== Author ===\n\nAfter completing her studies in psychology, she co-authored several of Mark Benecke's books between 2009 and 2011, of which she also edited \"The Benecke Universe\".<ref>Mark Benecke (Hrsg.): ''Das Benecke-Universum. Mitstreiter, Oma und Opa erz\u00e4hlen \u2026'', Militzke Verlag, Leipzig 2011, {{ISBN|978-3-86189-790-3}} ({{Google books|-RN4DwAAQBAJ|bibliographische Information}}).</ref>\n\nMark Benecke and others commissioned her to write \"Aus der Dunkelkammer des B\u00f6sen\" to create a comprehensive psychological profile for the Colombian serial killer [[Luis Alfredo Garavito Cubillos]]. The book was published 2011, and achieved high rankings on the [[Der Spiegel|Spiegel]] bestseller list. She has been a regular columnist for the German-language BDSM magazine \"[[Schlagzeilen]]\" since 2010.<ref name=\"Facebookprofil von Lydia Benecke\">[https://www.facebook.com/lydia.benecke.psychology/about Facebook-Profil von Lydia Benecke]</ref>\n\nIn her column \"Psychokiste\" she deals with various questions on the subject of BDSM from a psychological point of view.<ref name=\"Psychokiste\">[http://www.schlagzeilen.com/files/7565_14928_122_psychokiste.pdf Lydia Benecke: ''Psychokiste. Psychologische \u00dcberlegungen zur Aufnahme der Sklavenzentrale in die Liste jugendgef\u00e4hrdender Medien'', Artikel auf der Homepage des Schlagzeilen-Magazins] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924095025/http://www.schlagzeilen.com/files/7565_14928_122_psychokiste.pdf |date=24 September 2015 }}.</ref>\n\nIn 2013, she published a psychological profile of the historical serial killer and cannibal [[Karl Denke]].<ref name=\"Historische Serienm\u00f6rder III\">Armin R\u00fctters: ''Historische Serienm\u00f6rder III: Karl Denke \u2013 Der Kannibale von M\u00fcnsterberg: Ein deutscher Serienm\u00f6rder'', Kirchschlager, Arnstadt 2013, {{ISBN|978-3-934277-42-7}}.</ref> Her book \"Auf d\u00fcnnem Eis\" was published in October 2013. It entered the Spiegel bestseller list at number 13 in November 2013.\n\nHer next book \"Sadisten\" was published on 12 February 2015. \"T\u00f6dliche Liebe \u2013 Geschichten aus dem wahren Leben\" also achieved a place in the bestseller lists, as did \"Psychopathinnen. Die Psychologie des weiblichen B\u00f6sen\" (Female psychopaths. The psychology of female evil) in 2018.\n\n==Volunteer activities==\n\nLydia Benecke has been a member of the [[Gesellschaft zur wissenschaftlichen Untersuchung von Parawissenschaften|GWUP]] since her time as a student.<ref name=\"Skeptizismus\">[http://www.skeptoskop.com/skeptoskop-16-lydia-benecke/ ''Skeptoskop #16 \u2013 Lydia Benecke''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924102328/http://www.skeptoskop.com/skeptoskop-16-lydia-benecke/ |date=24 September 2015 }} Podcast von Skeptoskop.</ref> In this context, she deals with the psychological examination of the vampire motif, the vampire subculture, superstition and [[homeopathy]].<ref name=\"Vampir-Motiv 1\">[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fomiGf6WcJQ Youtube-Video \u201eDr Mark Benecke 1/4 Vampire unter uns\u201c von gwup] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214002936/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fomiGf6WcJQ |date=14 December 2016 }}.</ref><ref name=\"Vampir-Motiv 2\">[[Bernd Harder]]: [http://wiki2.benecke.com/index.php?title=2010-03_Skeptiker:_Vampire_ohne_Bis(s) ''Vampire ohne Bis(s)''. Erschienen in Skeptiker, M\u00e4rz 2010, Seiten 152 bis 157.] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180714164725/http://wiki2.benecke.com/index.php?title=2010-03_Skeptiker:_Vampire_ohne_Bis(s) |date=14 July 2018 }} Wiki von Mark Benecke.</ref><ref name=\"Vampir-Motiv 3\">[http://blog.gwup.net/2011/04/12/vampir-tv-mit-mark-und-lydia-benecke/ Bernd Harder: ''Vampir-TV mit Mark und Lydia Benecke''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180714221941/https://blog.gwup.net/2011/04/12/vampir-tv-mit-mark-und-lydia-benecke/ |date=14 July 2018 }} Artikel im Blog von gwup.</ref><ref name=\"Hom\u00f6opathie\">[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oSK5XPmkTMQ Youtube-Video \u201eDr. Mark Benecke kritisiert die Hom\u00f6opathie\u201c von beneckefan] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170512021814/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oSK5XPmkTMQ |date=12 May 2017 }}.</ref> In 2012, after writing a psychological statement on the indexing of a BDSM forum by the youth protection, she became the youth protection commissioner of the German BDSM youth organisation [[SMJG]].<ref name=\"Jugendschutzbeauftragte\" /> She is part of an international [[Working Group on Human Asphyxia]] set up by the Canadian forensic scientist Anny Sauvageau.<ref name=\"Working Group on Human Asphyxia Teil 1\">[http://forensics.crcpress.com/meet-our-authors/dr-anny-sauvageau-autoerotic-deaths/ ''Dr. Anny Sauvageau \u2013 Autoerotic Deaths''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201174945/http://forensics.crcpress.com/meet-our-authors/dr-anny-sauvageau-autoerotic-deaths/ |date=1 February 2014 }} Artikel auf der Homepage von CRC Press (englisch).</ref> She participated in the evaluation of a series of video recordings recording  [[Autoerotic fatality|fatal autoerotic]] accidents and suicides<ref name=\"Working Group on Human Asphyxia Teil 2\">A. Sauvageau, R. LaHarpe, V. J. Geberth: ''Agonal sequences in eight filmed hangings: analysis of respiratory and movement responses to asphyxia by hanging.'' In: ''Journal of forensic sciences.'' Band 55, Nummer 5, September 2010, S.&nbsp;1278\u20131281, {{DOI|10.1111/j.1556-4029.2010.01434.x}}, {{PMID|20487156}}.</ref><ref name=\"Working Group on Human Asphyxia Teil 3\">A. Sauvageau, R. Laharpe, D. King, G. Dowling, S. Andrews, S. Kelly, C. Ambrosi, J. P. Guay, V. J. Geberth: ''Agonal sequences in 14 filmed hangings with comments on the role of the type of suspension, ischemic habituation, and ethanol intoxication on the timing of agonal responses.'' In: ''The American journal of forensic medicine and pathology.'' Band 32, Nummer 2, Juni 2011, S.&nbsp;104\u2013107, {{DOI|10.1097/PAF.0b013e3181efba3a}}, {{PMID|20683242}}.</ref>\n\nShe was involved in suicide and [[Major depressive disorder|depression prevention]] in the non-profit association for the prevention of suicide and education about depression and suicide in adolescents and young people '''Freunde f\u00fcrs Leben e. V.'''<ref name=\"Freunde f\u00fcrs Leben 1\">[http://reportink.com/freunde-fuers-leben-e-v-suizid-und-depressionspraevention/ Freunde f\u00fcrs Leben e.&nbsp;V.: Suizid- und Depressionspr\u00e4vention] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190216101140/https://reportink.com/freunde-fuers-leben-e-v-suizid-und-depressionspraevention/ |date=16 February 2019 }} Blogeintrag auf der Website von reportink.</ref><ref name=\"Freunde f\u00fcrs Leben 2\">[http://www.frnd.de/friday-club-freunde-furs-leben-special-die-party-zum-thema-suizid-und-depressionspravention/ FRIDAY CLUB \u201eFreunde F\u00fcrs Leben\u201c Special \u2013 Die Party zum Thema Suizid- und Depressionspr\u00e4vention] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190215215737/http://www.frnd.de/friday-club-freunde-furs-leben-special-die-party-zum-thema-suizid-und-depressionspravention/ |date=15 February 2019 }} Artikel auf der Homepage von ''Freunde f\u00fcrs Leben e.&nbsp;V.''</ref>\n\n==Media==\n\nSince 2009 she has appeared as a psychological expert in various television programmes, including ''[[TV total]]'', ''{{ill|stern TV|de}}'', ''[[Explosiv - Das Magazin]]'', ''[[Markus Lanz]]'', ''[[Bambule]]'', ''[[Inka!]]'', ''Sat.1 breakfast television'', the special programme ''[[XY - gel\u00f6st]]'' and the [[ZDF]] documentary ''Dracula lebt!''\n<ref name=\"TV total\">[http://tvtotal.prosieben.de/tvtotal/videos/player/index.html?contentId=146810&initialTab=related Video zum Ausschnitt \u201eLydia Benecke und das B\u00f6se\u201c aus der TV-total-Sendung vom 3. Dezember 2013] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202092810/http://tvtotal.prosieben.de/tvtotal/videos/player/index.html?contentId=146810&initialTab=related |date=2 February 2014 }}, Video auf der Homepage von [[ProSieben]].</ref><ref name=\"Stern TV\">[http://www.stern.de/tv/sterntv/fake-profile-im-internet-echte-liebe-fuer-eine-faelschung-2074947.html Fake-Profile im Internet. Echte Liebe f\u00fcr eine F\u00e4lschung (stern-TV-Sendung vom 4. Dezember 2013)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140619024812/http://www.stern.de/tv/sterntv/fake-profile-im-internet-echte-liebe-fuer-eine-faelschung-2074947.html |date=19 June 2014 }} Artikel auf der Homepage des [[Stern (Zeitschrift)|Stern]].</ref><ref name=\"Markus Lanz 1\">[http://dw.de/p/133BG Sendung \u201eMarkus Lanz\u201c vom 26. November 2011]{{Dead link|date=April 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Artikel auf der Homepage der [[Deutsche Welle|Deutschen Welle]].</ref><ref name=\"Bambule\">[http://www.zdf.de/ZDF/zdfportal/programdata/a9378f22-6472-4148-8564-153867b0ffec/20229146 Bambule-Das Magazin. Die Lust am T\u00f6ten. Sendung vom 7. November 2013], Sendungsinformation auf der Homepage des [[ZDF]].</ref><ref name=\"Inka!\">[http://www.zdf.de/ZDF/zdfportal/programdata/32d88738-5e81-46f2-85d5-919efef8a35b/20207470 inka! Die Show am Nachmittag. Sendung vom 4. Oktober 2013] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140206121249/http://www.zdf.de/ZDF/zdfportal/programdata/32d88738-5e81-46f2-85d5-919efef8a35b/20207470 |date=6 February 2014 }} Sendungsinformation auf der Homepage des ZDF.</ref><ref name=\"Hom\u00f6opathie\" /><ref name=\"ZDF-Dokumentarfilm Dracula lebt 1\">[http://www.spiegel.de/kultur/tv/vampir-doku-dracula-lebt-schnaps-reinschuetten-herz-rausreissen-a-756436.html Jenni Zylka: ''Vampir-Doku \"Dracula lebt!\": Schnaps reinsch\u00fctten, Herz rausrei\u00dfen''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160920111453/http://www.spiegel.de/kultur/tv/vampir-doku-dracula-lebt-schnaps-reinschuetten-herz-rausreissen-a-756436.html |date=20 September 2016 }} Artikel auf der Homepage des Spiegel.</ref><ref name=\"Vampir-Motiv 3\" /><ref>\n{{citation|title=Vorschau: Spezialsendung XY-gel\u00f6st mit Lydia Benecke und Rudi Cerne|language=German|url=https://www.zdf.de/gesellschaft/aktenzeichen-xy-ungeloest/videos/aufsager-2-aktenzeichen-100.html|access-date=16 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171117070519/https://www.zdf.de/gesellschaft/aktenzeichen-xy-ungeloest/videos/aufsager-2-aktenzeichen-100.html|archive-date=17 November 2017|url-status=dead}}\n</ref>\n\nShe also works as an expert for radio, podcast productions, print media and electronic magazines. She has spoken from a psychological point of view on topics such as [[psychopathy]],<ref name=\"Ein Psychopath liebt sein Kind nicht mehr als sein Auto\" /> the [[Zodiac killer]],<ref name=\"Zodiac-Killer\">[http://www.hoaxilla.com/hoaxilla-81-zodiac-killer/ Hoaxilla #81 \u2013 \u201eZodiac Killer\u201c] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918012450/https://www.hoaxilla.com/hoaxilla-81-zodiac-killer/ |date=18 September 2018 }}, [[Podcast]] von Hoaxilla.</ref> sexually motivated homicides,<ref name=\"Sexualmorde\">[http://www.extratipp.com/news/rhein-main/zerstueckelter-junge-fluss-ist-tristan-killer-wieder-1531743.html Christian Reinartz: ''Zerst\u00fcckelter Junge aus dem Fluss: Ist der Tristan-Killer wieder da?''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201162056/http://www.extratipp.com/news/rhein-main/zerstueckelter-junge-fluss-ist-tristan-killer-wieder-1531743.html |date=1 February 2014 }} Artikel auf der Homepage des Rhein-Main EXTRA TIPP.</ref>  [[Letter bomb]] assassins,<ref name=\"Briefbomben-Attent\u00e4ter\">[http://www.focus.de/wissen/mensch/tid-24425/anschlag-auf-josef-ackermann-wie-briefbomben-attentaeter-ticken_aid_692199.html Stefanie Reiffert: ''Anschlag auf Josef Ackermann. Wie Briefbomben-Attent\u00e4ter ticken''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918110041/https://www.focus.de/wissen/mensch/tid-24425/anschlag-auf-josef-ackermann-wie-briefbomben-attentaeter-ticken_aid_692199.html |date=18 September 2018 }} Artikel auf der Homepage des Focus.</ref> the [[2011 Norway attacks]],<ref name=\"Anschl\u00e4ge in Norwegen\">[http://www.dradiowissen.de/psychologie-potentielle-taeter-im-netz-erkennen.33.de.html?dram%3Aarticle_id=11424 Potentielle T\u00e4ter im Netz erkennen. Gespr\u00e4ch mit der Diplom-Psychologin Lydia Benecke] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201161753/http://www.dradiowissen.de/psychologie-potentielle-taeter-im-netz-erkennen.33.de.html?dram:article_id=11424 |date=1 February 2014 }} Podcast auf der Homepage des DRadio Wissen.</ref> Vampires,<ref name=\"Vampire Podcast\">[http://www.hoaxilla.com/hoaxilla-50-vampire-unter-uns/ Hoaxilla #50 \u2013 \u2018Vampire unter uns!\u2019] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918012507/https://www.hoaxilla.com/hoaxilla-50-vampire-unter-uns/ |date=18 September 2018 }} Podcast von Hoaxilla.</ref><ref name=\"Vampir-Motiv 2\" /> BDSM,<ref name=\"BDSM Podcast\">[http://www.psycho-talk.de/2013/01/27/psyt008-sex/ PSYT008 Sex] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918012255/https://www.psycho-talk.de/2013/01/27/psyt008-sex/ |date=18 September 2018 }} Podcast von Psychotalk.</ref><ref name=\"Psychokiste\" /> sadomasochism in Germany,<ref name=\"SM in Deutschland Radiosendung\">[http://www.podcast.de/episode/42394987/Sadomasochists%2Bin%2BGermany/ Sadomasochists in Germany] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150825002616/http://www.podcast.de/episode/42394987/Sadomasochists+in+Germany |date=25 August 2015 }} Podcast auf podcast.de.</ref> skepticism,<ref name=\"Skeptizismus\" /> criminal psychology,<ref name=\"Bericht Journal 360 Grad\">Bericht Journal 360 Grad</ref><ref name=\"Bericht Welt\">Bericht Welt</ref><ref name=\"Kriminalpsychologie Interview 3\">[http://www.ksta.de/panorama/benecke-interview-die-seele-netter-massenmoerder,15189504,12027342.html Ismene Poulakos: ''Benecke-Interview. Die Seele netter Massenm\u00f6rder''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140219022338/http://www.ksta.de/panorama/benecke-interview-die-seele-netter-massenmoerder,15189504,12027342.html |date=19 February 2014 }} Artikel auf der Homepage des [[K\u00f6lner Stadt-Anzeiger]]s.</ref><ref name=\"Bericht Focus\" /> doomsday myths and end-time sects.<ref name=\"Weltuntergang Podcast\">[http://bartocast.de/?m=201212 F3 \u201cWeltuntergang zum Nachh\u00f6ren\u201d] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180917215415/http://bartocast.de/?m=201212 |date=17 September 2018 }}, Podcast auf bartocast.de.</ref>\n\nIn 2013 she was in Sat.1-Production \"Stalker \u2013 Caught in the act\" as psychologist responsible for the assessment of the perpetrators.<ref name=\"Stalker\" /><ref name=\"Stalker \u2013 Auf frischer Tat ertappt Trailer\">[http://www.sat1.de/tv/stalker-auf-frischer-tat-ertappt/video/trailer-stalker-ab-30-10-in-sat-1-clip ''Stalker \u2013 Auf frischer Tat ertappt''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201162152/http://www.sat1.de/tv/stalker-auf-frischer-tat-ertappt/video/trailer-stalker-ab-30-10-in-sat-1-clip |date=1 February 2014 }}, Trailer auf der Homepage von Sat.1.</ref>\nShe also explains criminal cases in German TV show ''Aktenzeichen XY \u2026 ungel\u00f6st''.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Berger |first1=Annette |title=Kriminalpsychologin Lydia Benecke erkl\u00e4rt in \"Aktenzeichen XY\": So ticken Straft\u00e4ter |url=https://www.stern.de/kultur/tv/aktenzeichen-xy--geloest--lydia-benecke-erklaert--wie-straftaeter-ticken-8468872.html |website=Stern.de |accessdate=17 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190218081848/https://www.stern.de/kultur/tv/aktenzeichen-xy--geloest--lydia-benecke-erklaert--wie-straftaeter-ticken-8468872.html |archive-date=18 February 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> She also works with ''Anw\u00e4lte der Toten'' and ''Erbarmungslos''\", two other TV shows.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rohm |first1=Brigitte |title=Die \"Psychologie des B\u00f6sen\"Krimipsychologin erz\u00e4hlt: Warum Serienkiller liebende Familienv\u00e4ter sein k\u00f6nnen |url=https://www.focus.de/wissen/mensch/die-psychologie-des-boesen-krimipsychologin-erzaehlt-warum-serienkiller-oft-liebende-familienvaeter-sind_id_7963910.html |website=www.focus.de |accessdate=17 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190218023005/https://www.focus.de/wissen/mensch/die-psychologie-des-boesen-krimipsychologin-erzaehlt-warum-serienkiller-oft-liebende-familienvaeter-sind_id_7963910.html |archive-date=18 February 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> She also appears in German shows ''Aktenzeichen XY...ungel\u00f6st'' and ''Anw\u00e4lte der Toten'' as well as ''Erbarmungslos''.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Berger |first1=Annette |title=Kriminalpsychologin Lydia Benecke erkl\u00e4rt in \"Aktenzeichen XY\": So ticken Straft\u00e4ter |url=https://www.stern.de/kultur/tv/aktenzeichen-xy--geloest--lydia-benecke-erklaert--wie-straftaeter-ticken-8468872.html |website=Stern.de |accessdate=18 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190218081848/https://www.stern.de/kultur/tv/aktenzeichen-xy--geloest--lydia-benecke-erklaert--wie-straftaeter-ticken-8468872.html |archive-date=18 February 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Rohm |first1=Brigitte |title=Die \"Psychologie des B\u00f6sen\"Krimipsychologin erz\u00e4hlt: Warum Serienkiller liebende Familienv\u00e4ter sein k\u00f6nnen. |url=https://www.focus.de/wissen/mensch/die-psychologie-des-boesen-krimipsychologin-erzaehlt-warum-serienkiller-oft-liebende-familienvaeter-sind_id_7963910.html |website=Focus.de |accessdate=18 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190218023005/https://www.focus.de/wissen/mensch/die-psychologie-des-boesen-krimipsychologin-erzaehlt-warum-serienkiller-oft-liebende-familienvaeter-sind_id_7963910.html |archive-date=18 February 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=J\u00fcrgens |first1=Frank |title=\"Erbarmungslos\" zeigt wahre Verbrechen und Verbrecher |url=https://www.noz.de/deutschland-welt/medien/artikel/1590950/erbarmungslos-zeigt-wahre-verbrechen-und-verbrecher |website=Noz.de |publisher=Neue Osnabr\u00fccker Zeitung |accessdate=18 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190218021326/https://www.noz.de/deutschland-welt/medien/artikel/1590950/erbarmungslos-zeigt-wahre-verbrechen-und-verbrecher |archive-date=18 February 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Publications==\n* ''Vampire unter uns! Teil 1: Rh. pos.'' (with Mark Benecke, Kathrin Sonntag, Nastassia Palanetskaya), Edition Roter Drache, Rudolstadt 2009, {{ISBN|978-3-939459-24-8}}.\n* ''Vampire unter uns! Teil 2: Rh. neg.'' (with Mark Benecke), Edition Roter Drache, Rudolstadt 2010, {{ISBN|978-3-939459-42-2}}\n* ''Das Benecke-Universum'' (with Mark Benecke), Militzke, Leipzig 2011, {{ISBN|978-3-86189-845-0}}.\n* ''Aus der Dunkelkammer des B\u00f6sen. Neue Berichte vom bekanntesten Kriminalbiologen der Welt'' (with Mark Benecke), L\u00fcbbe, K\u00f6ln 2011, {{ISBN|978-3-7857-6046-8}}, L. Benecke: p. 60-68/ 71\u2013259 / 292\u2013297 / 327\u2013330 / 357\u2013364 / 388\u2013390.\n* ''Auf d\u00fcnnem Eis. Die Psychologie des B\u00f6sen'', L\u00fcbbe, K\u00f6ln 2013, {{ISBN|978-3-7857-6095-6}}; Taschenbuch ebd. 2016, {{ISBN|978-3-404-60900-0}}.\n* ''Historische Serienm\u00f6rder III: Karl Denke \u2013 Der Kannibale von M\u00fcnsterberg: Ein deutscher Serienm\u00f6rder\" by Armin R\u00fctters, Kirchschlager 2013, L. Benecke: p.&nbsp;73\u201386, {{ISBN|978-3-934277-42-7}}.\n* ''Sadisten. T\u00f6dliche Liebe \u2013 Geschichten aus dem wahren Leben.'' L\u00fcbbe, K\u00f6ln 2015, {{ISBN|978-3-431-03899-6}}.\n* ''Wie meine Internet-Liebe zum Albtraum wurde: Das Ph\u00e4nomen Realfakes\" by Victoria Schwartz, Blanvalet 2015, L. Benecke: p. 256-266, {{ISBN|978-3-7645-0536-3}}.\n* ''Ein multidimensionales psychologisches Modell zur Unterscheidung zwischen inklinierendem und pericul\u00e4rem sexuellen Sadismus'', in: Schriftenreihe der Gesellschaft f\u00fcr Kriminologie, Polizei und Recht e.V. : Band 3 / II. Sammelband, Verlag f\u00fcr Polizeiwissenschaft, Frankfurt am Main 2015. L. Benecke: p. 32 \u2013 65. {{ISBN|978-3-86676-440-8}}.\n* ''Die 120 Tage von Sodom 2.0: Neu \u00fcbersetzt von Curt Moreck'', by Marquis de Sade with Frank Schulten, L. Benecke: p. 6\u201324), 2016, {{ISBN|978-3-932961-72-4}}.\n* ''Psychopathinnen. Die Psychologie des weiblichen B\u00f6sen.'' L\u00fcbbe, K\u00f6ln 2018, {{ISBN|978-3-431-03996-2}}.\n* ''Ein multidimensionales psychologisches Modell zur Unterscheidung zwischen inklinierendem und pericul\u00e4rem sexuellen Sadismus'', In: Destruktive Sexualit\u00e4t. Therapie und Risk-Assessment in der Forensischen Psychiatrie. Berlin 2018, L. Benecke: p.&nbsp;11 \u2013 26, {{ISBN|9783954664306}}.\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.benecke-psychology.com/ Own Website]\n* [https://www.gwup.org/who-is-who/1646-benecke-dr-lydia/ GWUP page]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Benecke, Lydia}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:German psychologists]]\n[[Category:Criminal psychologists]]\n[[Category:German non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:German women writers]]\n[[Category:People from Bytom]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|German criminal psychologist}}\n{{Infobox writer\n| embed            =\n| honorific_prefix =\n| name             = Lydia Benecke\n| honorific_suffix =\n| image            = LydiaBenecke.jpg\n| image_size       =\n| image_upright    =\n| alt              =\n| caption          = Lydia Benecke, 2017\n| native_name      =\n| native_name_lang =\n| pseudonym        =\n| birth_name       = E. C. Wawrzyniak\n| birth_date       = <!-- {{Birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| birth_place      = [[Bytom]], Poland\n| death_place      =\n| resting_place    =\n| occupation       =Criminal psychologist and writer\n| language         =\n| residence        =[[Cologne]] Germany\n| nationality      =\n| citizenship      = German\n| education        =Psychology\n| alma_mater       =\n| home_town        =\n| period           =\n| genre            = Popular science non-fiction.\n| subject          = <!-- or: | subjects = -->\n| movement         =\n| notableworks     = <!-- or: | notablework = -->\n| spouse           = <!-- or: | spouses = -->\n| partner          = <!-- or: | partners = -->\n| children         =\n| relatives        =\n| awards           =\n| signature        =\n| signature_alt    =\n| years_active     =\n| module           =\n| website          = <!-- {{URL|example.org}} -->\n| portaldisp       = <!-- \"on\", \"yes\", \"true\", etc.; or omit -->\n}}\n\n'''Lydia Benecke''' (born in 1982 as ''E. C. Wawrzyniak''<ref>{{cite web |last1=Benecke |first1=Lydia |title=Ist das Pers\u00f6nlichkeitskonstrukt \"Experience Seeking\"bei Sadomasochisten st\u00e4rker ausgepr\u00e4gtals bei Nicht-Sadomasochisten? |url=http://benecke-psychology.com/files/DIPLOMARBEIT_LYDIA_BENECKE_GEB_WAWRZYNIAK.PDF |website=Benecke Psychology |publisher=Diplomarbeit Ruhr-Universit\u00e4t Bochum |accessdate=17 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190218021518/http://benecke-psychology.com/files/DIPLOMARBEIT_LYDIA_BENECKE_GEB_WAWRZYNIAK.PDF |archive-date=18 February 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> in [[Bytom]], [[Poland]]) is a German criminal psychologist and writer of popular science non-fiction.\n\n==Life==\n\nBenecke was born in [[Poland]] and left for Germany at the age of 4 with her mother. She grew up in [[Bottrop]] and developed her interest in criminal cases from a young age.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hildebrand-Schute |first1=Ute |title=Kriminalpsychologin sammelte schon als Kind Kriminalf\u00e4lle |url=https://www.waz.de/staedte/bottrop/kriminalpsychologin-sammelte-schon-als-kind-kriminalfaelle-id215493627.html |publisher=WAZ |accessdate=15 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190216035357/https://www.waz.de/staedte/bottrop/kriminalpsychologin-sammelte-schon-als-kind-kriminalfaelle-id215493627.html |archive-date=16 February 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> After finishing school at the [[Janusz-Korczak-Gesamtschule (Bottrop)|Janusz-Korczak-Gesamtschule]] in [[Bottrop]], she studied Psychology, [[Psychopathology]] and [[Forensic science]] at the [[Ruhr University Bochum]].<ref name=\"Stalker\">[http://www.sat1.de/tv/stalker-auf-frischer-tat-ertappt/die-experten/lydia-benecke-diplom-psychologin Lydia Benecke, Diplom-Psychologin.] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190216035309/https://www.sat1.de/tv/stalker-auf-frischer-tat-ertappt/die-experten/lydia-benecke-diplom-psychologin |date=2019-02-16 }} Homepage of [[Sat.1]].</ref> She was married to [[Mark Benecke]]. She lives in [[Cologne]] and is active in the German skeptical organization [[Gesellschaft zur wissenschaftlichen Untersuchung von Parawissenschaften|GWUP]].\n\n==Career==\n\n===Psychologist===\n\nBenecke attended an adult education course in psychology as a teenager. After a school internship she worked as a freelancer for a psychological psychotherapist during her extracurricular time.\n\nSince 2008 she has been working therapeutically in a social therapy institution with sexual and violent offenders <ref>{{cite web|title=Ist das Pers\u00f6nlichkeitskonstrukt \"Experience Seeking\" bei Sadomasochisten st\u00e4rker ausgepr\u00e4gt als bei Nicht-Sadomasochisten? Eine Betrachtung des Experience Seeking und andere psychologische Faktoren bei inklinierenden Sadomasochisten|periodical=Benecke.com|url=http://benecke.com/pdf/DIPLOMARBEIT_LYDIA_BENECKE_GEB_WAWRZYNIAK.PDF|url-status=dead|format=PDF; 1,08&nbsp;MB|accessdate=26 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130320012040/http://benecke.com/pdf/DIPLOMARBEIT_LYDIA_BENECKE_GEB_WAWRZYNIAK.PDF|archivedate=20 March 2013|last=Lydia Benecke|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nBetween 2009 and 2013 she worked as a psychological consultant in criminal cases and in public relations for her then husband's company, the criminal biologist Mark Benecke<ref name=\"Jugendschutzbeauftragte\">[http://www.smjg.org/ueber-uns/personen/lydia-jugendschutzbeauftragte/ Lydia Benecke stellt sich selbst vor.] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190216094152/https://www.smjg.org/ueber-uns/personen/lydia-jugendschutzbeauftragte/ |date=2019-02-16 }} Homepage der SMJG.</ref><ref name=\"Bericht Focus\">[http://www.focus.de/wissen/mensch/tid-24277/kriminalbiologe-mark-benecke-die-schraegen-faelle-des-dr-tod_aid_687597.html Stefanie Reiffert: ''Kriminalbiologe Mark Benecke. Die schr\u00e4gen F\u00e4lle des \u201eDr. Tod\u201c''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190216040807/https://www.focus.de/wissen/mensch/tid-24277/kriminalbiologe-mark-benecke-die-schraegen-faelle-des-dr-tod_aid_687597.html |date=2019-02-16 }} Artikel auf der Homepage des [[Focus (German magazine)|Focus]].</ref> Nowadays, she works as an independent criminal psychologist with an office in Cologne in the fields of consulting and education. Her main areas of work are [[paraphilia]], [[personality disorders]] (especially psychopathy, dissocial personality disorders and borderline personality disorders), [[Psychological trauma]], superstitious beliefs, subcultures (especially BDSM scene, [[Dark culture]], [[Goth subculture]], sects and [[vampire subculture]].<ref name=\"Ein Psychopath liebt sein Kind nicht mehr als sein Auto\">[http://www.t-online.de/nachrichten/specials/id_66699686/so-ticken-psychopathen-eine-psychologin-erklaert.html Ruth Friedrich: ''T\u00e4ter ohne Reue im Kopf. \u201eEin Psychopath liebt sein Kind nicht mehr als sein Auto\u201c''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180330061436/http://www.t-online.de/nachrichten/specials/id_66699686/so-ticken-psychopathen-eine-psychologin-erklaert.html |date=2018-03-30 }} Interview mit Lydia Benecke auf der Homepage von [[T-Online]].</ref>\n\n=== Author ===\n\nAfter completing her studies in psychology, she co-authored several of Mark Benecke's books between 2009 and 2011, of which she also edited \"The Benecke Universe\".<ref>Mark Benecke (Hrsg.): ''Das Benecke-Universum. Mitstreiter, Oma und Opa erz\u00e4hlen \u2026'', Militzke Verlag, Leipzig 2011, {{ISBN|978-3-86189-790-3}} ({{Google books|-RN4DwAAQBAJ|bibliographische Information}}).</ref>\n\nMark Benecke and others commissioned her to write \"Aus der Dunkelkammer des B\u00f6sen\" to create a comprehensive psychological profile for the Colombian serial killer [[Luis Alfredo Garavito Cubillos]]. The book was published 2011, and achieved high rankings on the [[Der Spiegel|Spiegel]] bestseller list. She has been a regular columnist for the German-language BDSM magazine \"[[Schlagzeilen]]\" since 2010.<ref name=\"Facebookprofil von Lydia Benecke\">[https://www.facebook.com/lydia.benecke.psychology/about Facebook-Profil von Lydia Benecke]</ref>\n\nIn her column \"Psychokiste\" she deals with various questions on the subject of BDSM from a psychological point of view.<ref name=\"Psychokiste\">[http://www.schlagzeilen.com/files/7565_14928_122_psychokiste.pdf Lydia Benecke: ''Psychokiste. Psychologische \u00dcberlegungen zur Aufnahme der Sklavenzentrale in die Liste jugendgef\u00e4hrdender Medien'', Artikel auf der Homepage des Schlagzeilen-Magazins] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924095025/http://www.schlagzeilen.com/files/7565_14928_122_psychokiste.pdf |date=2015-09-24 }}.</ref>\n\nIn 2013, she published a psychological profile of the historical serial killer and cannibal [[Karl Denke]].<ref name=\"Historische Serienm\u00f6rder III\">Armin R\u00fctters: ''Historische Serienm\u00f6rder III: Karl Denke \u2013 Der Kannibale von M\u00fcnsterberg: Ein deutscher Serienm\u00f6rder'', Kirchschlager, Arnstadt 2013, {{ISBN|978-3-934277-42-7}}.</ref> Her book \"Auf d\u00fcnnem Eis\" was published in October 2013. It entered the Spiegel bestseller list at number 13 in November 2013.\n\nHer next book \"Sadisten\" was published on 12 February 2015. \"T\u00f6dliche Liebe \u2013 Geschichten aus dem wahren Leben\" also achieved a place in the bestseller lists, as did \"Psychopathinnen. Die Psychologie des weiblichen B\u00f6sen\" (Female psychopaths. The psychology of female evil) in 2018.\n\n==Volunteer activities==\n\nLydia Benecke has been a member of the [[Gesellschaft zur wissenschaftlichen Untersuchung von Parawissenschaften|GWUP]] since her time as a student.<ref name=\"Skeptizismus\">[http://www.skeptoskop.com/skeptoskop-16-lydia-benecke/ ''Skeptoskop #16 \u2013 Lydia Benecke''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924102328/http://www.skeptoskop.com/skeptoskop-16-lydia-benecke/ |date=2015-09-24 }} Podcast von Skeptoskop.</ref> In this context, she deals with the psychological examination of the vampire motif, the vampire subculture, superstition and [[homeopathy]].<ref name=\"Vampir-Motiv 1\">[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fomiGf6WcJQ Youtube-Video \u201eDr Mark Benecke 1/4 Vampire unter uns\u201c von gwup] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214002936/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fomiGf6WcJQ |date=2016-12-14 }}.</ref><ref name=\"Vampir-Motiv 2\">[[Bernd Harder]]: [http://wiki2.benecke.com/index.php?title=2010-03_Skeptiker:_Vampire_ohne_Bis(s) ''Vampire ohne Bis(s)''. Erschienen in Skeptiker, M\u00e4rz 2010, Seiten 152 bis 157.] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180714164725/http://wiki2.benecke.com/index.php?title=2010-03_Skeptiker:_Vampire_ohne_Bis(s) |date=2018-07-14 }} Wiki von Mark Benecke.</ref><ref name=\"Vampir-Motiv 3\">[http://blog.gwup.net/2011/04/12/vampir-tv-mit-mark-und-lydia-benecke/ Bernd Harder: ''Vampir-TV mit Mark und Lydia Benecke''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180714221941/https://blog.gwup.net/2011/04/12/vampir-tv-mit-mark-und-lydia-benecke/ |date=2018-07-14 }} Artikel im Blog von gwup.</ref><ref name=\"Hom\u00f6opathie\">[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oSK5XPmkTMQ Youtube-Video \u201eDr. Mark Benecke kritisiert die Hom\u00f6opathie\u201c von beneckefan] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170512021814/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oSK5XPmkTMQ |date=2017-05-12 }}.</ref> In 2012, after writing a psychological statement on the indexing of a BDSM forum by the youth protection, she became the youth protection commissioner of the German BDSM youth organisation [[SMJG]].<ref name=\"Jugendschutzbeauftragte\" /> She is part of an international [[Working Group on Human Asphyxia]] set up by the Canadian forensic scientist Anny Sauvageau.<ref name=\"Working Group on Human Asphyxia Teil 1\">[http://forensics.crcpress.com/meet-our-authors/dr-anny-sauvageau-autoerotic-deaths/ ''Dr. Anny Sauvageau \u2013 Autoerotic Deaths''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201174945/http://forensics.crcpress.com/meet-our-authors/dr-anny-sauvageau-autoerotic-deaths/ |date=2014-02-01 }} Artikel auf der Homepage von CRC Press (englisch).</ref> She participated in the evaluation of a series of video recordings recording  [[Autoerotic fatality|fatal autoerotic]] accidents and suicides<ref name=\"Working Group on Human Asphyxia Teil 2\">A. Sauvageau, R. LaHarpe, V. J. Geberth: ''Agonal sequences in eight filmed hangings: analysis of respiratory and movement responses to asphyxia by hanging.'' In: ''Journal of forensic sciences.'' Band 55, Nummer 5, September 2010, S.&nbsp;1278\u20131281, {{DOI|10.1111/j.1556-4029.2010.01434.x}}, {{PMID|20487156}}.</ref><ref name=\"Working Group on Human Asphyxia Teil 3\">A. Sauvageau, R. Laharpe, D. King, G. Dowling, S. Andrews, S. Kelly, C. Ambrosi, J. P. Guay, V. J. Geberth: ''Agonal sequences in 14 filmed hangings with comments on the role of the type of suspension, ischemic habituation, and ethanol intoxication on the timing of agonal responses.'' In: ''The American journal of forensic medicine and pathology.'' Band 32, Nummer 2, Juni 2011, S.&nbsp;104\u2013107, {{DOI|10.1097/PAF.0b013e3181efba3a}}, {{PMID|20683242}}.</ref>\n\nShe was involved in suicide and [[Major depressive disorder|depression prevention]] in the non-profit association for the prevention of suicide and education about depression and suicide in adolescents and young people '''Freunde f\u00fcrs Leben e. V.'''<ref name=\"Freunde f\u00fcrs Leben 1\">[http://reportink.com/freunde-fuers-leben-e-v-suizid-und-depressionspraevention/ Freunde f\u00fcrs Leben e.&nbsp;V.: Suizid- und Depressionspr\u00e4vention] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190216101140/https://reportink.com/freunde-fuers-leben-e-v-suizid-und-depressionspraevention/ |date=2019-02-16 }} Blogeintrag auf der Website von reportink.</ref><ref name=\"Freunde f\u00fcrs Leben 2\">[http://www.frnd.de/friday-club-freunde-furs-leben-special-die-party-zum-thema-suizid-und-depressionspravention/ FRIDAY CLUB \u201eFreunde F\u00fcrs Leben\u201c Special \u2013 Die Party zum Thema Suizid- und Depressionspr\u00e4vention] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190215215737/http://www.frnd.de/friday-club-freunde-furs-leben-special-die-party-zum-thema-suizid-und-depressionspravention/ |date=2019-02-15 }} Artikel auf der Homepage von ''Freunde f\u00fcrs Leben e.&nbsp;V.''</ref>\n\n==Media==\n\nSince 2009 she has appeared as a psychological expert in various television programmes, including ''[[TV total]]'', ''{{ill|stern TV|de}}'', ''[[Explosiv - Das Magazin]]'', ''[[Markus Lanz]]'', ''[[Bambule]]'', ''[[Inka!]]'', ''Sat.1 breakfast television'', the special programme ''[[XY - gel\u00f6st]]'' and the [[ZDF]] documentary ''Dracula lebt!''\n<ref name=\"TV total\">[http://tvtotal.prosieben.de/tvtotal/videos/player/index.html?contentId=146810&initialTab=related Video zum Ausschnitt \u201eLydia Benecke und das B\u00f6se\u201c aus der TV-total-Sendung vom 3. Dezember 2013] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202092810/http://tvtotal.prosieben.de/tvtotal/videos/player/index.html?contentId=146810&initialTab=related |date=2014-02-02 }}, Video auf der Homepage von [[ProSieben]].</ref><ref name=\"Stern TV\">[http://www.stern.de/tv/sterntv/fake-profile-im-internet-echte-liebe-fuer-eine-faelschung-2074947.html Fake-Profile im Internet. Echte Liebe f\u00fcr eine F\u00e4lschung (stern-TV-Sendung vom 4. Dezember 2013)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140619024812/http://www.stern.de/tv/sterntv/fake-profile-im-internet-echte-liebe-fuer-eine-faelschung-2074947.html |date=2014-06-19 }} Artikel auf der Homepage des [[Stern (Zeitschrift)|Stern]].</ref><ref name=\"Markus Lanz 1\">[http://dw.de/p/133BG Sendung \u201eMarkus Lanz\u201c vom 26. November 2011]{{Dead link|date=April 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Artikel auf der Homepage der [[Deutsche Welle|Deutschen Welle]].</ref><ref name=\"Bambule\">[http://www.zdf.de/ZDF/zdfportal/programdata/a9378f22-6472-4148-8564-153867b0ffec/20229146 Bambule-Das Magazin. Die Lust am T\u00f6ten. Sendung vom 7. November 2013], Sendungsinformation auf der Homepage des [[ZDF]].</ref><ref name=\"Inka!\">[http://www.zdf.de/ZDF/zdfportal/programdata/32d88738-5e81-46f2-85d5-919efef8a35b/20207470 inka! Die Show am Nachmittag. Sendung vom 4. Oktober 2013] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140206121249/http://www.zdf.de/ZDF/zdfportal/programdata/32d88738-5e81-46f2-85d5-919efef8a35b/20207470 |date=2014-02-06 }} Sendungsinformation auf der Homepage des ZDF.</ref><ref name=\"Hom\u00f6opathie\" /><ref name=\"ZDF-Dokumentarfilm Dracula lebt 1\">[http://www.spiegel.de/kultur/tv/vampir-doku-dracula-lebt-schnaps-reinschuetten-herz-rausreissen-a-756436.html Jenni Zylka: ''Vampir-Doku \"Dracula lebt!\": Schnaps reinsch\u00fctten, Herz rausrei\u00dfen''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160920111453/http://www.spiegel.de/kultur/tv/vampir-doku-dracula-lebt-schnaps-reinschuetten-herz-rausreissen-a-756436.html |date=2016-09-20 }} Artikel auf der Homepage des Spiegel.</ref><ref name=\"Vampir-Motiv 3\" /><ref>\n{{citation|title=Vorschau: Spezialsendung XY-gel\u00f6st mit Lydia Benecke und Rudi Cerne|language=German|url=https://www.zdf.de/gesellschaft/aktenzeichen-xy-ungeloest/videos/aufsager-2-aktenzeichen-100.html|access-date=2017-11-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171117070519/https://www.zdf.de/gesellschaft/aktenzeichen-xy-ungeloest/videos/aufsager-2-aktenzeichen-100.html|archive-date=2017-11-17|url-status=dead}}\n</ref>\n\nShe also works as an expert for radio, podcast productions, print media and electronic magazines. She has spoken from a psychological point of view on topics such as [[psychopathy]],<ref name=\"Ein Psychopath liebt sein Kind nicht mehr als sein Auto\" /> the [[Zodiac killer]],<ref name=\"Zodiac-Killer\">[http://www.hoaxilla.com/hoaxilla-81-zodiac-killer/ Hoaxilla #81 \u2013 \u201eZodiac Killer\u201c] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918012450/https://www.hoaxilla.com/hoaxilla-81-zodiac-killer/ |date=2018-09-18 }}, [[Podcast]] von Hoaxilla.</ref> sexually motivated homicides,<ref name=\"Sexualmorde\">[http://www.extratipp.com/news/rhein-main/zerstueckelter-junge-fluss-ist-tristan-killer-wieder-1531743.html Christian Reinartz: ''Zerst\u00fcckelter Junge aus dem Fluss: Ist der Tristan-Killer wieder da?''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201162056/http://www.extratipp.com/news/rhein-main/zerstueckelter-junge-fluss-ist-tristan-killer-wieder-1531743.html |date=2014-02-01 }} Artikel auf der Homepage des Rhein-Main EXTRA TIPP.</ref>  [[Letter bomb]] assassins,<ref name=\"Briefbomben-Attent\u00e4ter\">[http://www.focus.de/wissen/mensch/tid-24425/anschlag-auf-josef-ackermann-wie-briefbomben-attentaeter-ticken_aid_692199.html Stefanie Reiffert: ''Anschlag auf Josef Ackermann. Wie Briefbomben-Attent\u00e4ter ticken''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918110041/https://www.focus.de/wissen/mensch/tid-24425/anschlag-auf-josef-ackermann-wie-briefbomben-attentaeter-ticken_aid_692199.html |date=2018-09-18 }} Artikel auf der Homepage des Focus.</ref> the [[2011 Norway attacks]],<ref name=\"Anschl\u00e4ge in Norwegen\">[http://www.dradiowissen.de/psychologie-potentielle-taeter-im-netz-erkennen.33.de.html?dram%3Aarticle_id=11424 Potentielle T\u00e4ter im Netz erkennen. Gespr\u00e4ch mit der Diplom-Psychologin Lydia Benecke] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201161753/http://www.dradiowissen.de/psychologie-potentielle-taeter-im-netz-erkennen.33.de.html?dram:article_id=11424 |date=2014-02-01 }} Podcast auf der Homepage des DRadio Wissen.</ref> Vampires,<ref name=\"Vampire Podcast\">[http://www.hoaxilla.com/hoaxilla-50-vampire-unter-uns/ Hoaxilla #50 \u2013 \u2018Vampire unter uns!\u2019] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918012507/https://www.hoaxilla.com/hoaxilla-50-vampire-unter-uns/ |date=2018-09-18 }} Podcast von Hoaxilla.</ref><ref name=\"Vampir-Motiv 2\" /> BDSM,<ref name=\"BDSM Podcast\">[http://www.psycho-talk.de/2013/01/27/psyt008-sex/ PSYT008 Sex] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918012255/https://www.psycho-talk.de/2013/01/27/psyt008-sex/ |date=2018-09-18 }} Podcast von Psychotalk.</ref><ref name=\"Psychokiste\" /> sadomasochism in Germany,<ref name=\"SM in Deutschland Radiosendung\">[http://www.podcast.de/episode/42394987/Sadomasochists%2Bin%2BGermany/ Sadomasochists in Germany] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150825002616/http://www.podcast.de/episode/42394987/Sadomasochists+in+Germany |date=2015-08-25 }} Podcast auf podcast.de.</ref> skepticism,<ref name=\"Skeptizismus\" /> criminal psychology,<ref name=\"Bericht Journal 360 Grad\">Bericht Journal 360 Grad</ref><ref name=\"Bericht Welt\">Bericht Welt</ref><ref name=\"Kriminalpsychologie Interview 3\">[http://www.ksta.de/panorama/benecke-interview-die-seele-netter-massenmoerder,15189504,12027342.html Ismene Poulakos: ''Benecke-Interview. Die Seele netter Massenm\u00f6rder''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140219022338/http://www.ksta.de/panorama/benecke-interview-die-seele-netter-massenmoerder,15189504,12027342.html |date=2014-02-19 }} Artikel auf der Homepage des [[K\u00f6lner Stadt-Anzeiger]]s.</ref><ref name=\"Bericht Focus\" /> doomsday myths and end-time sects.<ref name=\"Weltuntergang Podcast\">[http://bartocast.de/?m=201212 F3 \u201cWeltuntergang zum Nachh\u00f6ren\u201d] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180917215415/http://bartocast.de/?m=201212 |date=2018-09-17 }}, Podcast auf bartocast.de.</ref>\n\nIn 2013 she was in Sat.1-Production \"Stalker \u2013 Caught in the act\" as psychologist responsible for the assessment of the perpetrators.<ref name=\"Stalker\" /><ref name=\"Stalker \u2013 Auf frischer Tat ertappt Trailer\">[http://www.sat1.de/tv/stalker-auf-frischer-tat-ertappt/video/trailer-stalker-ab-30-10-in-sat-1-clip ''Stalker \u2013 Auf frischer Tat ertappt''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201162152/http://www.sat1.de/tv/stalker-auf-frischer-tat-ertappt/video/trailer-stalker-ab-30-10-in-sat-1-clip |date=2014-02-01 }}, Trailer auf der Homepage von Sat.1.</ref>\nShe also explains criminal cases in German TV show ''Aktenzeichen XY \u2026 ungel\u00f6st''.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Berger |first1=Annette |title=Kriminalpsychologin Lydia Benecke erkl\u00e4rt in \"Aktenzeichen XY\": So ticken Straft\u00e4ter |url=https://www.stern.de/kultur/tv/aktenzeichen-xy--geloest--lydia-benecke-erklaert--wie-straftaeter-ticken-8468872.html |website=Stern.de |accessdate=17 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190218081848/https://www.stern.de/kultur/tv/aktenzeichen-xy--geloest--lydia-benecke-erklaert--wie-straftaeter-ticken-8468872.html |archive-date=18 February 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> She also works with ''Anw\u00e4lte der Toten'' and ''Erbarmungslos''\", two other TV shows.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rohm |first1=Brigitte |title=Die \"Psychologie des B\u00f6sen\"Krimipsychologin erz\u00e4hlt: Warum Serienkiller liebende Familienv\u00e4ter sein k\u00f6nnen |url=https://www.focus.de/wissen/mensch/die-psychologie-des-boesen-krimipsychologin-erzaehlt-warum-serienkiller-oft-liebende-familienvaeter-sind_id_7963910.html |website=www.focus.de |accessdate=17 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190218023005/https://www.focus.de/wissen/mensch/die-psychologie-des-boesen-krimipsychologin-erzaehlt-warum-serienkiller-oft-liebende-familienvaeter-sind_id_7963910.html |archive-date=18 February 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> She also appears in German shows ''Aktenzeichen XY...ungel\u00f6st'' and ''Anw\u00e4lte der Toten'' as well as ''Erbarmungslos''.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Berger |first1=Annette |title=Kriminalpsychologin Lydia Benecke erkl\u00e4rt in \"Aktenzeichen XY\": So ticken Straft\u00e4ter |url=https://www.stern.de/kultur/tv/aktenzeichen-xy--geloest--lydia-benecke-erklaert--wie-straftaeter-ticken-8468872.html |website=Stern.de |accessdate=18 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190218081848/https://www.stern.de/kultur/tv/aktenzeichen-xy--geloest--lydia-benecke-erklaert--wie-straftaeter-ticken-8468872.html |archive-date=18 February 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Rohm |first1=Brigitte |title=Die \"Psychologie des B\u00f6sen\"Krimipsychologin erz\u00e4hlt: Warum Serienkiller liebende Familienv\u00e4ter sein k\u00f6nnen. |url=https://www.focus.de/wissen/mensch/die-psychologie-des-boesen-krimipsychologin-erzaehlt-warum-serienkiller-oft-liebende-familienvaeter-sind_id_7963910.html |website=Focus.de |accessdate=18 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190218023005/https://www.focus.de/wissen/mensch/die-psychologie-des-boesen-krimipsychologin-erzaehlt-warum-serienkiller-oft-liebende-familienvaeter-sind_id_7963910.html |archive-date=18 February 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=J\u00fcrgens |first1=Frank |title=\"Erbarmungslos\" zeigt wahre Verbrechen und Verbrecher |url=https://www.noz.de/deutschland-welt/medien/artikel/1590950/erbarmungslos-zeigt-wahre-verbrechen-und-verbrecher |website=Noz.de |publisher=Neue Osnabr\u00fccker Zeitung |accessdate=18 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190218021326/https://www.noz.de/deutschland-welt/medien/artikel/1590950/erbarmungslos-zeigt-wahre-verbrechen-und-verbrecher |archive-date=18 February 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Publications==\n* ''Vampire unter uns! Teil 1: Rh. pos.'' (with Mark Benecke, Kathrin Sonntag, Nastassia Palanetskaya), Edition Roter Drache, Rudolstadt 2009, {{ISBN|978-3-939459-24-8}}.\n* ''Vampire unter uns! Teil 2: Rh. neg.'' (with Mark Benecke), Edition Roter Drache, Rudolstadt 2010, {{ISBN|978-3-939459-42-2}}\n* ''Das Benecke-Universum'' (with Mark Benecke), Militzke, Leipzig 2011, {{ISBN|978-3-86189-845-0}}.\n* ''Aus der Dunkelkammer des B\u00f6sen. Neue Berichte vom bekanntesten Kriminalbiologen der Welt'' (with Mark Benecke), L\u00fcbbe, K\u00f6ln 2011, {{ISBN|978-3-7857-6046-8}}, L. Benecke: p. 60-68/ 71\u2013259 / 292\u2013297 / 327\u2013330 / 357\u2013364 / 388\u2013390.\n* ''Auf d\u00fcnnem Eis. Die Psychologie des B\u00f6sen'', L\u00fcbbe, K\u00f6ln 2013, {{ISBN|978-